Kitano accuses him of cheating by disabling
the collars, pointing a gun at him.

00:17:14.860 --> 00:17:18.640
Shuya and Noriko enter, holding Kitano at
gunpoint.

00:17:18.640 --> 00:17:21.020
Kitano is not surprised to see them.

00:17:21.020 --> 00:17:25.910
He reveals his painting of the students' battle,
with a smiling Noriko as the sole survivor.

00:17:25.910 --> 00:17:29.541
The students are horrified at the image, with
Kitano revealing that he wanted Noriko, the

00:17:29.541 --> 00:17:32.080
only student he liked, to win the game from
the beginning.

00:17:32.080 --> 00:17:36.790
He tells Noriko to shoot him, but Shuya does
it instead, sparing Noriko.

00:17:36.790 --> 00:17:40.110
Kitano reveals that his gun is a toy before
collapsing.

00:17:40.110 --> 00:17:42.820
Knowing that the game is over, the trio removes
their collars.

00:17:42.820 --> 00:17:46.340
A phone rings nearby, and they're surprised
to see Kitano get up and answer his daughter's

00:17:46.340 --> 00:17:47.580
call.

00:17:47.580 --> 00:17:50.070
He argues with her before shooting the phone.

00:17:50.070 --> 00:17:53.700
He takes the last cookie from Noriko's gift,
then passes away.

00:17:53.700 --> 00:17:56.420
The students take a boat to leave the island.

00:17:56.420 --> 00:18:00.420
Kawada tells the two that he finally understands
why Keiko thanked him in the end before passing

00:18:00.420 --> 00:18:01.770
away.

00:18:01.770 --> 00:18:07.040
When they reach the city, Shuya and Noriko
